EDIT: Well after a month of procrastination I finally decided to go up to her and ask her out. I took your guys’ advice and played it cool. I didn’t use the pickup line. The conversation went somewhere along the lines of:

Me: “Hey, what’s your name?”
Her: “I’m xxxx”
Me: “I’m Gianni, it’s nice to meet you. I’ve seen you around campus and I thought you seemed cool. I’ve never gotten the chance to talk to you though.”

Then the conversation went on normally for a few minutes as we walked across campus together asking things like “What’s your major?” and “Where are you from?” et cetera. When we had to part ways, I took my chance and told her before saying bye, “Do you think I could get your number? Maybe we can hangout sometime.”

Then she said: “I’m sorry but I have a boyfriend.”

Story of my life.
